      "content": "so if it's fundamentally limited like that, does that mean the argument for moving back toward more nationalist/sovereign-focused policies is basically the only logical conclusion? like, if international bodies are just toothless, isn't it more realistic to just focus on individual country strength instead of trying to fix a broken system?",
